  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Waaahouuu 🎉 \r\n\r\nAwesome work @bobylito it's a great page for selling features of InstantSearch.js 👍 \r\nHow ever, while testing it I've found severals bugs or small issues:\r\n\r\n---------\r\n\r\nThere is a bug we might have not found before, when you click on the `infiniteHits -> load more` it changes also the results of the `hits` widget.\r\n\r\n---------\r\n\r\nThe `pagination` widget styles are modified from the documentation styles:\r\n\r\n```css\r\n.documentation-section .documentation-container ul li, .documentation-section .documentation-container ol li, .examples-section .documentation-container ul li, .examples-section .documentation-container ol li {\r\n    clear: both;\r\n    margin-bottom: 10px;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou should exclude the `margin-bottom: 10px` rules on any `.ais-pagination` children.\r\n\r\n---------\r\n\r\nThe buttons hover styles are broken as well, the documentation styles override the `a:hover` with:\r\n\r\n```css\r\na:hover, a:focus {\r\n    color: #007ab3;\r\n    text-decoration: underline;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis should be excluded from widgets on the page.\r\n\r\n-----------\r\n\r\nMaybe move the `clearAll` widget after the current refined values or at the end of the \"Filtering widgets\" section. It feels weird to clear all filters when did not played with them yet.\r\n\r\n------------\r\n\r\nFor the `currentRefinedValues` widget, I think that `false` is not a good showcase of an already refined value.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/893837/28823741-5cf2904c-76bf-11e7-9adb-a1b935ba377d.png)\r\n\r\n------------\r\n\r\nThe `menu` widget seems to be broken\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/893837/28823795-99530882-76bf-11e7-8e64-2f4f803e165f.png)\r\n",
    "created_at": "2017-08-01T11:46:57Z",
